        <num>CCRP 464</num>
        <heading>464.  Nature and contents of indictment</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 464.  Nature and contents of indictment
The indictment shall be a plain, concise, and definite written statement of the essential facts constituting the offense charged.  It shall state for each count the official or customary citation of the statute which the defendant is alleged to have violated.  Error in the citation or its omission shall not be ground for dismissal of the indictment or for reversal of a conviction if the error or omission did not mislead the defendant to his prejudice.</p>
        </content>
